## How does the female to male ratio of the crew compare with the success of the movie? 
The visualization below investigates the ratings of movies versus the ratio of female:male cast and crew members in movies. Users are able to toggle and compare the Rotten Tomatoes scores from critics, audiences, and also IMDB scores of movies.
[/div]

[/div]

[div style:`{width: '100%', paddingLeft: "15vw", paddingRight:"15vw"}`]
[TableauEmbed link:"https://public.tableau.com/views/final_viz_16224540252030/Dashboard1?:language=en-US&:display_count=n&:origin=viz_share_link" width:"1000" height:"800"/]
[/div]

[br /]

[div className: 'text']
[div className: 'idyll-text-container']
The data for the visualization was based off of the counts of guesses of a cast or crew member's gender for different movies and it is important to note that the full cast and crew was not listed for the movies so the ratios may not be completely accurate.
Just from looking at the distributions of the ratings versus the ratio of females to males, there is no strong correlation that indicates a film will be more or less successful with the a higher presence of females. The
lack of a correlation may then serve to support the idea that having more female representation within the cast and crew will have no harm towards the production.
[/div]


[/div]

